it's very clear you want to stick to your
plan isn't it the case though that

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:42.810
others are seeking to take that decision
out of your hands and Prime Minister is

00:04:42.810 --> 00:04:46.940
it not the case now that you are in
office but you're not really in power

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:51.420
when we bring the deal back what is
going to happen now is that there'll be

00:04:51.420 --> 00:04:55.950
negotiations particularly focusing on
the future framework and filling their

00:04:55.950 --> 00:05:00.060
details of that out and an EU Council
meeting and that will then be brought

00:05:00.060 --> 00:05:05.370
back to the House of Commons and to a
vote in the House of Commons I'm going

00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:10.050
to do my job of getting the best deal
for Britain I'm going to do my job of

00:05:10.050 --> 00:05:13.890
getting a deal that is in the national
interest when the vote comes before the

00:05:13.890 --> 00:05:18.570
House of Commons MPs will be doing their
job they will need to look at that a

00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:22.260
deal they will need to consider the vote
of the British people to leave the

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:26.970
European Union and our duty to deliver
on that vote and of course they will be

00:05:26.970 --> 00:05:31.850
held to account by their constituents
for the decisions that they take

